---
intent: >
  Build the llms.txt generator at src/service/llmsTxt — consume docsRegistry
  (not duplicate the walk), add a lightweight description accessor to
  docsRegistry's public API so per-route frontmatter descriptions are
  available without a full markdown render, compose a canonical-URL link
  list grouped by the four DOCS_CATEGORIES sections, render the complete
  llmstxt.org-shaped document (H1 + blockquote + three prose paragraphs +
  four H2 link lists), emit it to public/llms.txt via a Node prebuild
  script so the static export serves /llms.txt at the site root, and
  gate the artifact with build-time verification that catches shape,
  URL, and drift failures before next build proceeds.
---

## Project Structure

Annotated tree of the module after the plan executes, rooted at
`src/service/llmsTxt/`. Everything inside this tree is new except where
marked `[existing]`. The shape mirrors the `src/service/socialShare/`
precedent — an orchestrator that exposes a pure-data config plus a
sibling render pipeline invoked only via npm scripts — because the two
modules solve the same class of problem (build-time static asset that
must land in `public/` under the static-export contract).

```
src/service/llmsTxt/
├── .aide                              ← [existing] intent spec
├── plan.aide                          ← [existing] this file
├── index.ts                           ← orchestrator. Single job: expose the
│                                          llmstxt.org content contract as a
│                                          plain-data config for any caller.
│                                          Shape:
│                                            export const llmsTxtConfig: LlmsTxtConfig
│                                            export default llmsTxtConfig
│                                          Does NOT import Playwright, fs
│                                          writes, or docsRegistry at module
│                                          load — keeps this importable from
│                                          the Next build graph without
│                                          pulling Node-only code into the
│                                          bundle. The sibling renderLlmsTxt
│                                          helper is reached only via
│                                          npm run llms:render.
│
├── llmsTxtConfig/
│   └── index.ts                       ← () => LlmsTxtConfig
│                                          Pure constant builder. Centralizes
│                                          every copy surface the generator
│                                          emits that is NOT derived from
│                                          docsRegistry: the H1 product name,
│                                          the blockquote sentence, the three
│                                          prose paragraphs (overview,
│                                          why-it-matters, getting-started),
│                                          the canonical origin, the npm
│                                          install command, and the output
│                                          path. All link-list text comes
│                                          from docsRegistry at render time;
│                                          this file never names a doc slug.
│
├── renderLlmsTxt/
│   ├── index.ts                       ← renderLlmsTxt(): Promise<void>
│   │                                       Node-only script entry invoked by
│   │                                       npm run llms:render. Pipeline:
│   │                                       load registry → group routes by
│   │                                       section → fetch per-route
│   │                                       descriptions → compose document
│   │                                       → write to public/llms.txt →
│   │                                       verify output.
│   │
│   ├── run.mjs                        ← Three-line ESM shim invoked by npm
│   │                                       script. Imports the compiled TS
│   │                                       entry via tsx and calls it —
│   │                                       exact same pattern as
│   │                                       socialShare/renderOgImage/run.mjs.
│   │                                       Keeps the prebuild hook pointing
│   │                                       at a stable .mjs file while the
│   │                                       render logic lives in typed .ts.
│   │
│   ├── loadRouteGroups/
│   │   └── index.ts                   ← (registry: DocRegistry) =>
│   │                                       Promise<RouteGroup[]>
│   │                                       Groups DocRegistry.routes by
│   │                                       section in DOCS_CATEGORIES order,
│   │                                       enriches each route with its
│   │                                       description via the prerequisite
│   │                                       getDocMeta helper, and preserves
│   │                                       the registry's deterministic
│   │                                       within-section ordering. Returns
│   │                                       one RouteGroup per section.
│   │
│   ├── composeDocument/
│   │   ├── index.ts                   ← (config: LlmsTxtConfig,
│   │   │                                 groups: RouteGroup[]) => string
│   │   │                                 Orchestrator that assembles the
│   │   │                                 full llms.txt file in the exact
│   │   │                                 llmstxt.org order:
│   │   │                                   H1 → blockquote → preamble (3
│   │   │                                   paragraphs) → H2 link lists
│   │   │                                   (one per RouteGroup).
│   │   │                                 Pure function — no I/O. Returns
│   │   │                                 the final UTF-8 string ending in
│   │   │                                 a single trailing newline.
│   │   │
│   │   ├── renderHeading/
│   │   │   └── index.ts               ← (config: LlmsTxtConfig) => string
│   │   │                                  Produces the H1 line
│   │   │                                  (`# <productName>`) plus a blank
│   │   │                                  line. Nothing else.
│   │   │
│   │   ├── renderBlockquote/
│   │   │   └── index.ts               ← (config: LlmsTxtConfig) => string
│   │   │                                  Produces the one-sentence summary
│   │   │                                  prefixed with `> ` plus a blank
│   │   │                                  line.
│   │   │
│   │   ├── renderPreamble/
│   │   │   └── index.ts               ← (config: LlmsTxtConfig) => string
│   │   │                                  Renders the three prose paragraphs
│   │   │                                  (overview, whyItMatters,
│   │   │                                  gettingStarted) as bare paragraphs
│   │   │                                  separated by blank lines — no
│   │   │                                  subheadings, per the llmstxt.org
│   │   │                                  spec.
│   │   │
│   │   ├── renderSection/
│   │   │   └── index.ts               ← (group: RouteGroup) => string
│   │   │                                  Renders one H2 heading
│   │   │                                  (`## <label>`) plus the group's
│   │   │                                  link list. Delegates each list
│   │   │                                  entry to renderLink.
│   │   │
│   │   └── renderLink/
│   │       └── index.ts               ← (entry: LinkEntry) => string
│   │                                       Renders one bullet line in the
│   │                                       exact llmstxt.org format:
│   │                                         `- [<title>](<absoluteUrl>): <description>`
│   │                                       absoluteUrl is prebuilt by
│   │                                       loadRouteGroups — this helper
│   │                                       never constructs URLs.
│   │
│   └── verifyOutput/
│       └── index.ts                   ← (outPath: string,
│                                          expectedSectionOrder: DocSection[])
│                                          => Promise<{ bytes: number;
│                                                       routeCount: number }>
│                                       Reads the generated file and gates
│                                       the build. Throws on ANY of:
│                                       - file missing or empty
│                                       - first line does not start with
│                                         `# ` (H1 missing)
│                                       - second non-blank line does not
│                                         start with `> ` (blockquote
│                                         missing)
│                                       - H2 headings absent, in wrong
│                                         order, or any section has zero
│                                         links
│                                       - any link line lacks the
│                                         `[title](url): description`
│                                         shape
│                                       - any link URL is relative, ends
│                                         in `.md`, or does not start with
│                                         the canonical origin
│                                       - file contains the abandoned
│                                         mascot names `AIDEY` or the
│                                         standalone token ` AID ` (case
│                                         sensitive — the root intent's
│                                         prohibition is absolute)
│                                       - file advertises a companion
│                                         file (`/llms-full.txt`, `/ai.txt`)
│                                       Returns bytes and routeCount on
│                                       success so the render orchestrator
│                                       can log them.
│
└── types.ts                           ← Module-local types:
                                           - LlmsTxtConfig     (product
                                             name, summary, preamble,
                                             origin, outputPath, install
                                             command)
                                           - LinkEntry         (title,
                                             absoluteUrl, description)
                                           - RouteGroup        (section,
                                             label, entries: LinkEntry[])
                                         No runtime logic. Local to this
                                         module because the shapes are
                                         llms.txt-specific and should not
                                         leak into src/types/ (which is
                                         reserved for cross-module types).
```

Changes outside the module:

```
public/
├── llms.txt                           ← NEW, generated artifact — plain
│                                          UTF-8, trailing newline. Written
│                                          by renderLlmsTxt. Not hand-edited,
│                                          not checked in as a source. Next
│                                          copies it to out/llms.txt on
│                                          build, served as text/plain by
│                                          GitHub Pages at /llms.txt.
└── ...                                ← [existing] unchanged.

src/service/docsRegistry/              ← [existing, additive — see
                                           Prerequisites section] — gains
                                           one new exported helper
                                           getDocMeta. No other behavior
                                           changes.

package.json                           ← [existing, modified] —
                                           + scripts.llms:render:
                                             "node --import tsx
                                              src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/run.mjs"
                                           + scripts.prebuild is extended
                                             from "npm run og:render" to
                                             "npm run og:render && npm run llms:render"
                                             so both static assets are
                                             regenerated on every build in
                                             a deterministic order.
```

The `design/` folder convention from socialShare does NOT apply here —
llms.txt has no visual artifact, no fonts, no binary assets. Its only
input is text, and the canonical text comes from docsRegistry, so there
is nothing to check into a `design/` subfolder.

## Prerequisites

This plan consumes one existing module and requires one additive public
API surface to be added to it before the render pipeline can run. The
prerequisite does not require its own `plan.aide` — the change is a
pure additive export that extends the existing orchestrator's public
surface by one function.

- **`@/service/docsRegistry` must expose `getDocMeta(route: DocRoute):
  Promise<{ title: string; description: string | undefined }>`.** This
  returns the route's title (already carried on `DocRoute`) and the
  frontmatter `description` parsed from the same markdown file
  `renderDoc` reads. Implementation must NOT invoke the Shiki
  highlighter and must NOT render markdown to HTML — the whole point of
  the accessor is a cheap, frontmatter-only read. The accessor is added
  as a named export on `src/service/docsRegistry/index.ts` alongside
  the existing `renderDoc` named export. This is step 1 of the Plan
  below — the llmsTxt module does not land until it exists.

- **`@/service/docsRegistry` continues to export its current public
  surface unchanged:** the default `buildRegistry` function, the named
  `renderDoc` function, and the types via `@/types/docs`
  (`DocRegistry`, `DocRoute`, `DocSection`, `DocRouteKey`,
  `DocFrontmatter`, `RenderedDoc`). llmsTxt consumes `buildRegistry`
  (to get the deterministic 33-route list), `DocRoute` (for typing),
  and `DocSection` (for the section ordering contract) — but it never
  calls `renderDoc` because HTML rendering is wasted work for this use
  case.

- **`@/data/docsCategories` continues to export `DOCS_CATEGORIES` and
  `SECTION_INDEX_META`.** llmsTxt reads `DOCS_CATEGORIES` for section
  ordering (methodology → commands → agents → skills) and uses each
  entry's `section` and `urlSegment` values. No additions required.

- **Node 22 + npm 10 on the build host.** `node:fs/promises` and native
  ESM are assumed (same baseline as the existing `socialShare`
  pipeline). No new runtime dependencies — the render script uses
  only Node built-ins plus `tsx` for on-the-fly TypeScript (already
  a devDependency).

## Plan

### 1. Extend docsRegistry with a frontmatter-only meta accessor

Read: `coding-playbook/services/service-layer`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

This step lives inside `src/service/docsRegistry/`, not `src/service/llmsTxt/`,
because the frontmatter read belongs to the registry's domain — parsing
the same markdown file `renderDoc` reads is the registry's job, not
llmsTxt's. Keeping the read inside docsRegistry preserves horizontal
isolation (llmsTxt never reaches into another service's internals) and
concentrates filesystem+parsing concerns in one orchestrator.

- [x] 1a. Add a new helper folder `src/service/docsRegistry/getDocMeta/`
      containing `index.ts`. Default export signature:
      `getDocMeta(route: DocRoute): Promise<{ title: string; description: string | undefined }>`.
      The helper reads `route.absPath` via `node:fs/promises.readFile`,
      delegates to the existing sibling `parseDocFrontmatter` helper
      for YAML extraction, and returns the resolved `title` and the
      `description` field from the returned frontmatter (undefined
      when absent). No Shiki, no markdown-to-HTML, no body processing.
      JSDoc narrates the contract: this is the cheap-read counterpart
      to `renderDoc`, intended for consumers that need title +
      description only (such as the llms.txt generator and any future
      sitemap or meta-index surface).
- [x] 1b. Export `getDocMeta` as a named export from
      `src/service/docsRegistry/index.ts` — alongside the existing
      default `buildRegistry` and named `renderDoc`. JSDoc on the
      new export cross-references `renderDoc` so readers of the
      orchestrator know when to pick which accessor.
- [x] 1c. Add `src/service/docsRegistry/getDocMeta/index.test.ts`
      co-located per the testing convention. Vitest with
      `vi.mock('node:fs/promises', ...)` returning fixture markdown
      content for three cases: (i) frontmatter with `title` and
      `description` both present — returns both verbatim; (ii)
      frontmatter with `title` only — returns title, `description`
      undefined; (iii) no frontmatter, body starts with `# H1` —
      returns `title` derived from H1 and `description` undefined.
      These are the three shapes the 33 real docs exhibit; the test
      pins the accessor's behavior against each.

### 2. Declare llmsTxt module types

Read: `coding-playbook/workflow/type-system`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

- [x] Create `src/service/llmsTxt/types.ts` defining three plain-data
      shapes used throughout the module:
        - `LlmsTxtConfig`: product identity and static copy surfaces.
          Fields: `productName: string` (for the H1), `summary: string`
          (for the blockquote, one sentence), `overview: string` (first
          preamble paragraph), `whyItMatters: string` (second preamble
          paragraph), `gettingStarted: string` (third preamble
          paragraph), `origin: "https://aidemd.dev"` (literal type —
          drift guard), `outputPath: string` (site-root path where the
          file is served; literal `"/llms.txt"`), `filesystemPath:
          string` (absolute or process-cwd-relative path where the
          render script writes the file; `public/llms.txt`).
        - `LinkEntry`: one rendered bullet. Fields:
          `title: string`, `absoluteUrl: string`, `description: string`
          (required — an empty string is valid, `undefined` is not,
          so the renderer never has to branch on presence).
        - `RouteGroup`: one H2 section's worth of links. Fields:
          `section: DocSection`, `label: string` (the H2 heading text —
          comes from `SECTION_INDEX_META[section].label` so Methodology/
          Commands/Agents/Skills match the site's own labels verbatim),
          `entries: LinkEntry[]` (in the registry's deterministic
          within-section order, already sorted by
          `docsRegistry.buildRegistry`).
      No runtime logic — types only. Import
      `DocSection` from `@/types/docs`.

### 3. Author the static config (everything not derived from docsRegistry)

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/services/service-layer`

- [x] Create `src/service/llmsTxt/llmsTxtConfig/index.ts` — default export
      returning a frozen `LlmsTxtConfig`. Copy constants (exact strings
      traceable to the `.aide` Good examples section):
        - `productName`: `"AIDE — Autonomous Intent-Driven Engineering"`
        - `summary`: one sentence that names the methodology AND the
          package in the same breath, per Strategy decision #2. The
          canonical string is modeled on the spec's Good examples
          blockquote — an implementor-facing verbatim reference. The
          final string is a plain declarative sentence; do not insert
          exclamation points, hype adjectives, or the mascot name.
        - `overview`: one short paragraph explaining what AIDE (the
          methodology) and `@aidemd-mcp/server` (the package) are,
          using the root-intent framing "a short intent spec next to
          the code is the contract every agent works from." No
          adjectives from the undesired list ("seamless",
          "revolutionary", "cutting-edge", "game-changing"). No
          exclamation points. No mascot name.
        - `whyItMatters`: one short paragraph addressed to the agent
          reading the file — "if you are operating in a codebase that
          ships `.aide` files, this methodology governs how you read
          those specs, plan from them, build against them, and
          validate your output." Matches the spec's Good examples
          third paragraph.
        - `gettingStarted`: two short sentences. Sentence one: install
          via `npx @aidemd-mcp/server init`. Sentence two: docs site
          URL `https://aidemd.dev/`.
        - `origin`: `"https://aidemd.dev"` as a literal.
        - `outputPath`: `"/llms.txt"` as a literal.
        - `filesystemPath`: resolved at render time via
          `path.resolve(process.cwd(), 'public/llms.txt')` — so the
          config stores the repo-relative string
          `"public/llms.txt"` and the render orchestrator does the
          resolution. Keeps this config pure-data and independent of
          `process.cwd()` at import time.
      Return `Object.freeze(...)` of the object so mutation attempts
      throw in strict mode — same drift guard the socialShare config
      uses.

### 4. Author the llmsTxt orchestrator (import-safe public surface)

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

- [x] Create `src/service/llmsTxt/index.ts`. The orchestrator imports
      `llmsTxtConfig`, calls it once at module load, and exports both
      the resolved config as a named export `llmsTxt` AND as the
      default export — mirroring the shape `src/service/socialShare/index.ts`
      established. JSDoc narrates: this module's single consumer-
      facing responsibility is handing the content contract to
      whoever needs it; the render script at `renderLlmsTxt/` is a
      sibling helper reached only via `npm run llms:render` and is
      deliberately not imported from this orchestrator (keeps
      `node:fs/promises` writes out of the Next build graph).
      No render-script wiring. No prerequisites on docsRegistry at
      this layer — the orchestrator is pure config.

### 5. Implement the route-group loader (consumes docsRegistry)

Read: `coding-playbook/services/service-layer`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

- [x] Create `src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/loadRouteGroups/index.ts`.
      Default export: `loadRouteGroups(registry: DocRegistry):
      Promise<RouteGroup[]>`. Pipeline (pure composition — each bullet
      below names one tier of transformation):
        1. For each category in `DOCS_CATEGORIES` (in array order,
           which is methodology → commands → agents → skills):
             - Filter `registry.routes` to those whose `section` matches.
               The filter preserves the within-section ordering the
               registry already produced (index-first, alphabetical).
             - For each filtered route, call `getDocMeta(route)` to
               obtain `{ title, description }`. `Promise.all` the
               per-route calls to parallelize the frontmatter reads.
             - Construct a `LinkEntry` per route:
                 - `title`: prefer `meta.title`; fall back to
                   `route.title` (which is already resolved from H1
                   or slug by `walkDocsRoot`).
                 - `absoluteUrl`: the registry's `route.urlPath` is
                   site-root relative (`/docs/<section>/<slug>`);
                   prefix with `llmsTxtConfig.origin` to produce the
                   absolute URL the spec requires
                   (`https://aidemd.dev/docs/<section>/<slug>`).
                 - `description`: prefer `meta.description`; fall back
                   to the empty string if the doc has no frontmatter
                   description at all. Rendering decides whether to
                   emit the `: description` suffix based on emptiness
                   (see step 6d).
             - Emit one `RouteGroup`:
                 - `section`: category.section
                 - `label`: `SECTION_INDEX_META[category.section].label`
                   — guarantees the H2 heading text matches the site's
                   own section heading exactly
                 - `entries`: the constructed `LinkEntry[]`
        2. Return the array of four `RouteGroup`s in category order.
      The loader never mutates `registry`, never re-walks the
      filesystem, and never reads a markdown file that docsRegistry
      has not already registered as a route. That is the drift-
      resistance contract: add a file, docsRegistry sees it,
      `loadRouteGroups` sees it, llms.txt emits it — no manual step.

### 6. Implement the document composer (pure string assembly)

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

- [x] 6a. Create `src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/composeDocument/renderHeading/index.ts`.
      Default export: `renderHeading(config: LlmsTxtConfig): string`.
      Returns the single line `# <productName>` followed by `\n\n`
      (one blank line separator).
- [x] 6b. Create `.../composeDocument/renderBlockquote/index.ts`.
      Default export: `renderBlockquote(config: LlmsTxtConfig): string`.
      Returns `> <summary>` followed by `\n\n`.
- [x] 6c. Create `.../composeDocument/renderPreamble/index.ts`.
      Default export: `renderPreamble(config: LlmsTxtConfig): string`.
      Returns the three prose paragraphs (overview, whyItMatters,
      gettingStarted) joined with `\n\n` between them and terminated
      with `\n\n`. No subheadings. No additional structure.
- [x] 6d. Create `.../composeDocument/renderLink/index.ts`. Default
      export: `renderLink(entry: LinkEntry): string`. Returns exactly
      one line:
        - When `entry.description` is non-empty:
          `- [<title>](<absoluteUrl>): <description>`
        - When `entry.description` is empty:
          `- [<title>](<absoluteUrl>)` (no trailing colon)
      No logic beyond the presence check. The line ends in `\n`.
- [x] 6e. Create `.../composeDocument/renderSection/index.ts`. Default
      export: `renderSection(group: RouteGroup): string`. Returns
      `## <label>\n\n` followed by each entry rendered via `renderLink`,
      followed by one blank line. Sections never share a heading — one
      H2 per group, always.
- [x] 6f. Create `.../composeDocument/index.ts` — the composer
      orchestrator. Default export:
      `composeDocument(config: LlmsTxtConfig, groups: RouteGroup[]): string`.
      Pipeline:
        1. `renderHeading(config)`
        2. `renderBlockquote(config)`
        3. `renderPreamble(config)`
        4. `groups.map(renderSection).join("")`
        5. Normalize trailing whitespace so the final string ends in
           exactly one `\n`.
      Pure function — no I/O. Inline step-by-step comments narrate
      the pipeline per the Tier-3 convention.

### 7. Implement the output verifier (gates the build)

Read: `coding-playbook/services/service-layer`, `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`

- [x] Create `src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/verifyOutput/index.ts`.
      Default export signature:
      `verifyOutput(outPath: string, expectedSectionOrder: DocSection[]): Promise<{ bytes: number; routeCount: number }>`.
      Reads the file via `node:fs/promises.readFile` + `stat`. Applies
      the checks below. Throws a descriptive `Error` on ANY failure so
      the prebuild script exits non-zero and `next build` aborts —
      that is the drift gate the spec's `outcomes.desired` require:
        - **File exists and is non-empty.** `stat.size > 0`.
        - **H1 shape.** The first line starts with exactly `# `.
        - **Blockquote shape.** The first line after the H1 that is
          not blank starts with `> `.
        - **Section headings.** The document contains exactly one
          `## <label>` for each of the four DOCS_CATEGORIES labels,
          in `expectedSectionOrder`. No extra H2s, no missing H2s,
          no reordering.
        - **Link lines.** Every bullet under an H2 matches the
          pattern
          `^- \[[^\]]+\]\(https://aidemd\.dev/docs/[^)]+\)(:.+)?$`.
          Captures: title, url, optional description. A bullet that
          fails this regex is a spec violation.
        - **URL shape.** No link URL ends in `.md`. No link URL is
          relative (does not start with `/` alone, does not start
          with `.`). Every URL starts with
          `https://aidemd.dev/docs/<section>/` where `<section>` is
          one of the four DOCS_CATEGORIES `urlSegment` values. Any
          deviation throws.
        - **Section has at least one link.** Each of the four H2
          sections must be followed by at least one bullet line
          before the next H2. An empty section means the walk broke.
        - **No abandoned mascot names.** The document must NOT match
          `/AIDEY/i` or the standalone token ` AID ` (case-
          sensitive, with word boundaries) — covers overview copy,
          link descriptions, and any accidental leak.
        - **No companion-file advertisement.** The document must
          NOT contain any of: `/llms-full.txt`, `llms-full.txt`,
          `/ai.txt`, or the phrase "full version". The root spec's
          single-entry-point contract is absolute.
      On success, returns `{ bytes, routeCount }` where `routeCount`
      is the total number of bullet lines matched. The render
      orchestrator logs both in its summary line.

### 8. Implement the render orchestrator (end-to-end pipeline)

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/services/service-layer`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

- [x] 8a. Create `src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/index.ts`. Default
      export: `renderLlmsTxt(): Promise<void>`. Orchestrator JSDoc
      narrates the pipeline end-to-end. Pipeline sequence (each step
      carries an inline comment):
        1. Import and call `buildRegistry` from `@/service/docsRegistry`
           to get the deterministically-ordered `DocRegistry`.
        2. `groups = await loadRouteGroups(registry)` — enriches each
           route with title+description via `getDocMeta`.
        3. Import `llmsTxtConfig` from `@/service/llmsTxt`. (Local
           import — same module's sibling.)
        4. `document = composeDocument(llmsTxtConfig, groups)` — pure
           string assembly.
        5. `outPath = path.resolve(process.cwd(), llmsTxtConfig.filesystemPath)`
        6. Ensure the parent directory exists (`mkdir({ recursive:
           true })` on `path.dirname(outPath)`) — a defensive guard
           against a fresh clone where `public/` is absent.
        7. `writeFile(outPath, document, { encoding: 'utf8' })`.
        8. `metrics = await verifyOutput(outPath,
              DOCS_CATEGORIES.map(c => c.section))`
        9. `console.log` a single build-log line of the form
           `"llms.txt rendered — <routeCount> links, <bytes> bytes"`
           so CI output carries the verification result.
      Any thrown error from a helper bubbles; the prebuild script
      exits non-zero and `next build` aborts. That is the gate.

- [x] 8b. Create `src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/run.mjs` — the
      three-line ESM shim. Imports the compiled TS entry and awaits
      it. Exact same pattern (and rationale) as
      `src/service/socialShare/renderOgImage/run.mjs`: the npm
      script targets a stable `.mjs` entry, `tsx` transpiles the
      imported `.ts` on the fly. No inline logic in the shim beyond
      import + call + `process.exit(0)` on success (or allow the
      unhandled rejection to exit non-zero on failure — Node's
      default behavior).

### 9. Wire the npm script and prebuild hook

Read: `coding-playbook/foundations/conventions`, `coding-playbook/architecture/folder-structure`

- [x] 9a. Edit `package.json`:
        - Add `"llms:render": "node --import tsx src/service/llmsTxt/renderLlmsTxt/run.mjs"`
          to `scripts`.
        - Extend `"prebuild"` from the current
          `"npm run og:render"` to
          `"npm run og:render && npm run llms:render"`.
          The `&&` chain is intentional: if og:render fails we want
          llms:render to be skipped (not silently run against a
          stale og.png); if llms:render fails, `next build` must
          abort. No `||` fallbacks anywhere in the chain.
- [x] 9b. Run `npm run llms:render` in isolation from the module's
      working directory. Verify: exits 0, writes
      `public/llms.txt`, and logs the
      `"llms.txt rendered — <N> links, <B> bytes"` line. N MUST
      equal the current total route count (33 today; the plan
      documents the number but does not hardcode it anywhere —
      the registry produces whatever it finds).

